## Session 3 — GENERATION (SPEC_ROUND3): rendering, shapes, id allocation, content, levels

### Corpus reads (captured OUTPUT: oracle/dot_corpus/ 12022 payloads, captured_responses/)
- Shape census over all 12022 dot + all 81 manifests: shapes = record(160409),
  ellipse(188270), plain(11564). NO trapezium/invtrapezium anywhere in the crawl.
- Node-id/PORT allocation (mine_ids.py): verified over ALL 12022 graphs that ids
  are one global counter in emission order (== file order), a record consuming one
  id per cell (premises->info->conclusions) THEN one node id; other kinds one id.
  12022/12022 byte-consistent. (Re-verified in Rust: tests/alloc_corpus.rs,
  12022/12022 via the crate's own NodeIdAllocator.)
- Record group structure (mine_groups.py): 100% of 160409 records carry an info
  cell (#t : Rule); groups = present-of [premises,info,conclusions], EMPTY premise
  or conclusion group dropped. dist: 3grp 153854 (prem|info|concl), 2grp info@0
  2147 (info|concl, e.g. Fresh), 2grp info@1 4406 (prem|info), 1grp 2.
- Record-cell WRAP mining (mine_wrap.py/mine_indent.py/mine_width.py): 188192
  wrapped cells. Continuation indent = &nbsp; run equal to the column of the
  broken group's FIRST element (after "( " for a fact, after "<" for a tuple,
  after "[" for an action list) — verified on many cells. Segments joined by \l,
  trailing \l after the last line. Break-point chars: , ) space > ] . First-line
  length ranges 5..87 (NOT a flat width) => the break DECISION is the pretty-
  printer's width/group internal (GAP); the FORMAT+indent are exact.
- Fact-vs-function spacing: facts pad `Name( a, b )` / `Name( )`; functions do
  not `f(a, b)`; tuples `<a, b>`; info cell `#t : Rule[acts]` or bare `#t : Rule`.
- Content vocabulary census (mine_content.py): edge attr signatures = 11 fixed
  styles (red-dashed !KU deduction; bold w10 [+gray50] structural; gray30 message;
  blue3-dashed / black-dashed temporal; orangered2; invis; purple/green/darkorange
  goal edges). Ellipse colors: none / gray (!KU) / darkblue (action). Ellipse
  kinds: !KU(m)@#t, Action(..)@#t, compressed `#t : rule[..]`.
- Query-param census: grep of manifests found the UI menu "Graph simplification
  off/L1/L2/L3" (lvl0..lvl3 toggles). Captured graph URLs carry NO query params.

