### Implemented (graph-clean)
- render::wrap_cell — byte-exact wrap+peel: layout_fact (fill args / recurse into a
  sole tuple / peel `)` to col 0), layout_tuple (fill + `>` peel to `<`-col),
  layout_info (vertical action `sep`), run_layout (greedy fill), split_top_commas.
  Wired into generate::build_record for premise/info/conclusion cells.
- generate: cluster emission (RuleInstance/RawRule .cluster(label,color); free-then-
  cluster bucketing in emission/id order); GraphNode::Temporal (#var, incl. .last());
  GraphNode::Shaped (generic shape escape hatch, incl. trapezium dual); RawRule +
  GraphNode::RawRule (pre-rendered cell strings through the same wrap/escape pipeline).
- Tests: wrap_E12/E13/E14/W71/W72/W74 generation fixtures, cluster_process (live)
  + cluster_multi (corpus 79c) generation fixtures, last_timepoint (corpus 24a)
  fixture, RawRule==Term byte-parity + RawRule wrap, wrap_cell unit tests. Full
  GRAPHCLEAN_CORPUS round-trip stays 12022/12022 byte-exact.
